 9561 1m; and Yesler Way\nADC TO ASK\nAMENDMENT\nT O H R 1 99\nWASHINGTON. D. 0.. April 20\nThe JACL Anti Discrimination\nCommittee said today it would urge\nan amendment to HR 199. the Judd\nhi\u201c, to provide that wives. children\nor husbands of American citizens\nbo permitted to immigrate to the\nUnited States quota-tree.\nSuch a policy is in effect only for\nEuropean countries. Chinese wivrrs\nand Filipino wives and children.\nIn its present form\u2018 the Judd bill\nprovides that husbands. wives and\nunmarried children may enter thn\nUnited States quota free only if\ncoming from countries having an\nannual quota greater than 200.\nThis provision would eliminati-\nChinese wives and Filipino wives\nand children from the quota-free\nstatus they now havo. a provision\nnppmed by Chinese and Filipino\nAmericans on the west coast.\nMike Masaoka. national JACL\nADC legislativg director. said the\nobjective of the amendment is to\napply 9h? same principles to Asiatic\nimmigration as applied to European\nimmigration.\nHe said proposed change is \"more\nrealistic than merely seeking an\namendment to the bill to retain tne\nquota-free provisions for China and\nthe Philippines. yet not granting\nequal rights to other Asiatic or\nPacific isiand countries.\u201c\nIn support of the proposed JACL\nADC amendment. Masaoka said one\nof the basic tenets of America is\nto keep families united.\nIf the amendment is adopted. it\nwould eliminate the need for spec\nial legislation to permit soldier\nbrides' to enter the United States.\nMeantime. the JACL ADC is\nDressing for early consideration of\nthe measure by the Senate Sub~\ncommittee on Immigiation and Nu\nturalization. which must act on the\nHousenmproved bill beiore the ant\ncan go further in the Senate.\nChi JACL Plans\nTo Honor Heads\nCHICAGO. 111,. April 20 As is\nthe custom of the Chicago JACL\nchanter. Marl Subusmvn. 1948. and\nmembers of her cabhmt and stand\ning committees. will be honored u!\nn l'vmgnltinn dinnvr on Fr